common_issues.title: JetBrains plugin installation issue
common_issues.description: Users are unable to install a specific JetBrains plugin because it's not found in the JetBrains Marketplace.  This issue is occurring on macOS with Pieces OS version 12.2.1 and is related to an Early Access Program feature. The error message "404 Publisher Model not found" suggests a potential issue with the plugin's availability or the user's access to it.

related_issues.title: pieces Jetbrains plugin

pieces Jetbrains plugin
### Checked for Existing Issues?

- [x] Yes, I have checked existing issues and cannot find one related to this.

### Software

Desktop Application, JetBrains

### Operating System / Platform

macOS

### Your Pieces OS Version

12.2.1

### Early Access Program

- [x] Yes, this is related to an Early Access Program feature.

### Kindly describe the bug and include as much detail as possible on what you were doing so we can reproduce the bug.

I'd like to install a JetBrains plugin, but it doesn't exist in the JetBrains Marketplace.
Error generating summary: 404 Publisher Model `projects/pi3c3s-cloud-server/locations/us-east1/publishers/google/models/gemini-pro` was not found or your project does not have access to it. Please ensure you are using a valid model version. For more information, see: https://cloud.google.com/vertex-ai/generative-ai/docs/learn/model-versions

recommendations: Investigate the "404 Publisher Model not found" error related to the JetBrains plugin installation on macOS.  This appears to be impacting users on Pieces OS 12.2.1 and involves an Early Access Program feature.
Check the plugin's availability in the JetBrains Marketplace and ensure users have the necessary access. The error message suggests a potential issue with the plugin itself or user permissions.
Prioritize resolution of issue #849, "pieces Jetbrains plugin", as it has the highest activity level and represents the primary support concern during this period.
